---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SectionAnimator } from '../components/islands/SectionAnimator';
import { StakesCTAPulse } from '../components/islands/StakesCTAPulse';
import { TIDYCAL_URL } from '../config';
---

<Base title="About Gary Tate — Consultates" description="Engineer. Commercial leader. AI practitioner. 35 years across military electronics, enterprise sales, and production AI — now helping leaders make sense of it.">

  <!-- Section 1 — Hero (asymmetric two-column) -->
  <section style="padding: var(--section-py) var(--content-px);">
    <div style="max-width: var(--content-max); margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[280px_1fr] gap-12 items-center">
        <div class="flex justify-center lg:justify-start">
          <img
            src="/images/gary-tate.webp"
            alt="Gary Tate"
            width="200"
            height="200"
            class="rounded-full object-cover"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-hero">Engineer. Commercial leader. AI practitioner.</h1>
          <p class="text-body-lg text-muted-foreground mt-4">35 years across military electronics, enterprise sales leadership, and production AI.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2 — The Story (editorial timeline) -->
  <section style="padding: var(--section-py) var(--content-px);">
    <div style="max-width: var(--content-max); margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 class="text-section mb-12">The through-line</h2>

      <div class="timeline-container">
        <!-- Entry 1: 1980s -->
        <SectionAnimator client:visible>
          <div class="timeline-entry">
            <div class="timeline-marker">
              <span class="timeline-dot"></span>
              <span class="timeline-era">1980s</span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <p class="text-body text-muted-foreground">Gary started coding at 10. He joined the Royal Air Force and spent a decade in military electronics, telecoms, cryptography, and secure communications — physical systems where mistakes aren't theoretical.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </SectionAnimator>

        <!-- Entry 2: 1990s -->
        <SectionAnimator client:visible delay={0.1}>
          <div class="timeline-entry">
            <div class="timeline-marker">
              <span class="timeline-dot"></span>
              <span class="timeline-era">1990s</span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <p class="text-body text-muted-foreground">Then another decade building telecoms and internet infrastructure. His own company first, then 8 years as a Senior Systems Engineer at Juniper Networks in Silicon Valley. Later, 5 years as Director of Systems Engineering at Cyan.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </SectionAnimator>

        <!-- Entry 3: 2000s -->
        <SectionAnimator client:visible delay={0.2}>
          <div class="timeline-entry">
            <div class="timeline-marker">
              <span class="timeline-dot"></span>
              <span class="timeline-era">2000s</span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <p class="text-body text-muted-foreground">He moved from engineering into sales — not because he stopped being technical, but because he could sit in front of a CRO and explain the technology in terms that closed deals. Systems engineer → Director → MD Sales → VP Sales (three times) → CRO. Always deep-tech companies — cybersecurity, AI, enterprise SaaS, networking infrastructure. 16 countries. He built entire sales organisations from zero.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </SectionAnimator>

        <!-- Entry 4: Today -->
        <SectionAnimator client:visible delay={0.3}>
          <div class="timeline-entry">
            <div class="timeline-marker">
              <span class="timeline-dot"></span>
              <span class="timeline-era">Today</span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <p class="text-body text-muted-foreground">Today, Gary ships production applications with AI agents. He designs agentic workflows with real API integrations. He builds alone what would have taken a small team two years ago.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </SectionAnimator>

        <!-- Entry 5: Why it matters -->
        <SectionAnimator client:visible delay={0.4}>
          <div class="timeline-entry">
            <div class="timeline-marker">
              <span class="timeline-dot"></span>
              <span class="timeline-era timeline-era--summary">Why it matters</span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <p class="text-body text-muted-foreground">Most AI consultants fall into one camp: technical people who can't explain it to a boardroom, business people who've never built anything, or trainers teaching from slides they didn't write. Gary does all three. That's why the consulting, the training, and the leadership all carry weight.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </SectionAnimator>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3 — Family Business (warm card) -->
  <section style="padding: var(--section-py) var(--content-px);">
    <div style="max-width: var(--content-max); margin: 0 auto;">
      <SectionAnimator client:visible>
        <div class="family-card">
          <h2 class="text-section mb-6">A family business</h2>
          <p class="text-body text-secondary-foreground">Consultates is Gary and Trinh Tate. They don't scale through volume. They scale through trust. You get one accountable team from start to finish — not a rotating cast of consultants.</p>
        </div>
      </SectionAnimator>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4 — Lead with AI PRO (accent banner) -->
  <section style="padding: var(--section-py) var(--content-px);">
    <div style="max-width: var(--content-max); margin: 0 auto;">
      <SectionAnimator client:visible>
        <div class="aipro-banner">
          <h2 class="text-section mb-6">Lead with AI PRO</h2>
          <p class="text-body text-muted-foreground">Gary is a guest lecturer and hosts monthly agentic briefings through Lead with AI PRO — a platform with 3× weekly analyst briefings, tutorials, and an active WhatsApp community. His sessions feature live demos of OpenClaw (his own agentic framework) and synthesise what the leading voices in AI — Karpathy, Amodei, Suleiman, Roose — are saying, translated for non-technical leaders.</p>
        </div>
      </SectionAnimator>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5 — Dark CTA -->
  <section style="background: #0D1117;">
    <div class="glow corner-marks max-w-[800px] mx-auto text-center" style="padding: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 8rem) clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 8rem); --corner-color: rgba(139,108,199,0.4);">
      <SectionAnimator client:visible>
        <h2 class="text-section" style="color: #FFFFFF;">
          Ready to <em style="font-style: normal; color: #8B6CC7;">talk</em>?
        </h2>
      </SectionAnimator>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <StakesCTAPulse
          client:visible
          href={TIDYCAL_URL}
          text="Book a Free Call"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
  /* Timeline */
  .timeline-container {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 80px;
  }

  .timeline-container::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 60px;
    top: 8px;
    bottom: 8px;
    width: 2px;
    background: var(--border);
  }

  .timeline-entry {
    position: relative;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .timeline-entry:last-child {
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .timeline-marker {
    position: absolute;
    left: -80px;
    top: 4px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    width: 40px;
  }

  .timeline-dot {
    display: block;
    width: 12px;
    height: 12px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 2px solid var(--primary);
    background: var(--background);
    position: absolute;
    left: -26px;
    top: 4px;
  }

  .timeline-era {
    position: absolute;
    left: -80px;
    top: 0;
    width: 44px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono), monospace;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
    text-align: right;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .timeline-era--summary {
    width: 80px;
    left: -116px;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
  }

  .timeline-content {
    /* Content flows in normal document flow at the padded-left position */
  }

  /* Mobile adjustments */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .timeline-container {
      padding-left: 60px;
    }

    .timeline-container::before {
      left: 40px;
    }

    .timeline-dot {
      left: -26px;
    }

    .timeline-era {
      left: -60px;
      width: 30px;
      font-size: 0.65rem;
    }

    .timeline-era--summary {
      width: 56px;
      left: -60px;
      font-size: 0.6rem;
    }
  }

  /* Family business card */
  .family-card {
    background: var(--secondary);
    border-radius: var(--card-radius);
    padding: var(--card-padding);
    box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
  }

  /* AI PRO banner */
  .aipro-banner {
    background: var(--card);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--primary);
    border-radius: var(--card-radius);
    padding: var(--card-padding);
    box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
  }
</style>
